title: Chennai weather latest update: Final spell of northeast monsoon may bring rain to coastal Tamil Nadu - MSN
article_text:
Chennai Weather LATEST Update: Tamil Nadu may witness one of final rain spells of northeast monsoon, with light to moderate showers forecast mainly in northern, coastal regions till December 28, colder nights, frost warnings add to winter conditions
The Regional Meteorological Centre has predicted light to moderate rainfall across parts of Tamil Nadu until December 28. Officials indicated that the rain activity on Christmas Day would largely affect north Tamil Nadu, while southern districts are expected to remain dry. After a short break, coastal Tamil Nadu and Puducherry may see another spell of rain around December 30.
With dry conditions prevailing over most regions, meteorologists have observed a likely fall in minimum temperatures by two to three degrees Celsius below normal in some areas. Chennai is expected to experience cool, pleasant mornings with mist or haze, along with a chance of light rain. The RMC explained that strengthening easterly winds could trigger mild showers over north coastal districts. Enhanced night-time cooling over hill regions may lead to ground frost, prompting warnings for isolated areas of Kodaikanal and the Nilgiris.
Among hill stations, Udhagamandalam reported the lowest minimum temperature at 5.4 degrees Celsius, followed by Kodaikanal and Coonoor. Several places in the plains, including Salem and Namakkal, also recorded below-normal night temperatures, while Tiruttani marked the lowest minimum among plains stations. Since October 1, Tamil Nadu has received 42.7 cm of rainfall, marginally below the seasonal average but still classified as normal. The department considers December 31 as the official conclusion of the northeast monsoon, though occasional rainfall may continue into January, as seen in previous years.

title: Monsoon Alert – Heavy rain expected in several states within 24 hours, clouds to gather - Times Bull
article_text:
Monsoon Forecast – The Christmas festival is being celebrated today, but the weather may disrupt the festivities. The weather is continuously deteriorating. Snowfall in the hilly states and dense fog and falling temperatures in the plains are wreaking havoc. Late-night rains in some parts of the country have made the weather pleasant.

Clouds still linger. Dense fog has completely halted life in Delhi-NCR and surrounding areas, causing considerable inconvenience to everyone. The weather remains inclement in several states, where rain is expected. Rajasthan and Bihar are experiencing intense cold. The Indian Meteorological Department (IMD) has issued a heavy rainfall warning for several states across the country.

Weather in Arunachal Pradesh

The weather in the northeastern state of Arunachal Pradesh has once again taken a turn for the worse. The state had witnessed heavy rainfall during the monsoon season. Now, intermittent rain has been observed for the past few days. The weather in Arunachal Pradesh may show its fury again. The IMD has issued a heavy rainfall warning for December 25th, Christmas Day.

Heavy Rainfall Expected in These States

According to the IMD, the weather in Tamil Nadu may once again turn severe. The Meteorological Department has predicted heavy rainfall in Tamil Nadu on December 25th, Christmas Day.

Along with this, a rain warning has been issued for several places across the country.

A heavy rainfall alert has been issued for Himachal Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Assam, Meghalaya, and Kerala. Besides these, intermittent rain warnings have been issued for Puducherry, Andaman and Nicobar Islands, and Karaikal on December 25th. People have been advised to take precautions.

Weather in Rajasthan

The IMD predicts that several districts of Rajasthan will experience the effects of the cold. The Meteorological Department has predicted a drop in morning and evening temperatures in several districts of Rajasthan on December 25th, Christmas Day. Dense fog may also prevail in many parts of the state during the day. In many places, there is a possibility of occasional sunshine during the day.
